# Node.js Conventions

## Runtime
- Node.js 20+ LTS ‚Äî use native `fetch`, `crypto`
- Always specify `"engines": { "node": ">=20" }` in package.json

## Environment Variables
- Validate all required env vars at startup ‚Äî fail fast
```typescript
const required = ['DATABASE_URL', 'API_KEY'];
for (const key of required) {
  if (!process.env[key]) throw new Error(`Missing env var: ${key}`);
}
```
- Never read `process.env` deep in business logic ‚Äî read at startup, pass down

## Process Management
- Handle `SIGTERM` and `SIGINT` for graceful shutdown
- Register `process.on('unhandledRejection', ...)` at startup ‚Äî log + exit(1)

## Logging
- Structured JSON logging (pino or similar) in production
- Log level via `LOG_LEVEL` env var
- Always include: timestamp, level, message, module

## Package Conventions
- Commit `package-lock.json`
- Pin exact versions for infrastructure packages
- Scripts: always define `start`, `build`, `dev`, `typecheck`, `lint`

